{"name":"Answer user questions for Task Automation (01659)","nodes":[{"parameters":{"public":true,"options":{}},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chatTrigger","typeVersion":1.1,"position":[-270,400],"id":"9c53f8bd-1ff7-4235-aa4b-368f8c20f6a7","name":"When Chat Message Received","webhookId":"7279394a-9562-4358-9c71-86b56b4c0d72"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"6e1beb07-27fe-498f-abbd-61352f3d5992","name":"requestId","value":"={{ $json.requestId || $json.id || $execution.id }}","type":"string"},{"id":"b1ff0cef-1b66-4bb0-8b73-5ff8541c31bf","name":"receivedAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[54,400],"id":"29a7932e-8b0f-4319-b9b9-b15b69f279b2","name":"Stamp & Shape Request"},{"parameters":{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"e25c877b-1709-4a4c-8c16-947e6acb14dc","leftValue":"={{ $json.requestId }}","rightValue":"","operator":{"type":"string","operation":"notEmpty"}}],"combinator":"and"}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.if","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[378,400],"id":"8f2cd27c-5359-4831-ac0b-4c77a7b665fe","name":"Payload Valid?"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Request Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[378,910],"id":"74685577-bc6b-498e-b7b2-78d9dc54a5c7","name":"Record Rejected Input","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"promptType":"define","text":"={{ $json.chatInput || $json.question || JSON.stringify($json) }}","options":{"systemMessage":"You answer request questions using only the retrieved knowledge-base context. If the context does not contain the answer, say so and set needsHuman=true.","maxIterations":6}},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[702,400],"id":"619e54f4-3561-4635-a8b9-10d1030be13b","name":"Answer from Knowledge Base","onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"model":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"gpt-4o-mini","cachedResultName":"gpt-4o-mini"},"options":{}},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatOpenAi","typeVersion":1.2,"position":[945,970],"id":"4156ab70-da5a-41f9-b15f-c08bcebe5509","name":"OpenAI Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"memoryKey":"kb_main","mode":"retrieve-as-tool","topK":5,"toolDescription":"Semantic search over the task automation knowledge base. Always call this before answering factual request questions."},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.vectorStoreInMemory","typeVersion":1.3,"position":[999,1390],"id":"503cfcc7-cf08-4b79-bd15-4a0ead8dcfed","name":"Knowledge Base Retriever"},{"parameters":{"options":{}},"type":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.embeddingsOpenAi","typeVersion":1.2,"position":[1053,1900],"id":"4e720138-760f-4354-ba06-2f09c64b77b9","name":"Query Embeddings"},{"parameters":{"conditions":{"options":{"caseSensitive":true,"leftValue":"","typeValidation":"strict","version":2},"conditions":[{"id":"5086f250-300e-4518-8459-434e7fbcd715","leftValue":"={{ !($json.output || '').includes('needsHuman') }}","rightValue":true,"operator":{"type":"boolean","operation":"true"}}],"combinator":"and"}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.if","typeVersion":2.2,"position":[1377,400],"id":"1ba1175c-724a-4f74-a08a-8ff332f9369f","name":"Grounded Answer Found?"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#ai-ops","cachedResultName":"#ai-ops"},"text":"={{ $json.output }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[1701,160],"id":"55fac69d-a274-4537-87bd-291f680d8f56","name":"Deliver Answer via Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Request Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[2025,760],"id":"9f95856a-f359-4dca-8931-ca753eaa229f","name":"Log Knowledge Gap","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#ai-ops","cachedResultName":"#ai-ops"},"text":"=📚 Unanswered question logged: {{ $json.chatInput || $json.question }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[2673,760],"id":"6d28f7fb-5427-426d-b804-2687ac51d729","name":"Flag Gap to KB Owners","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"read","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Request Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[3645,400],"id":"12570b22-c40e-4ca6-aa71-3e4c48146ef2","name":"Load Previous Snapshot","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"alwaysOutputData":true,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"mode":"runOnceForAllItems","jsCode":"// Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\nconst current = $input.first().json;\nconst prev = $('Load Previous Snapshot').first().json || {};\nconst drift = {};\nfor (const k of Object.keys(current)) {\n  if (typeof current[k] === 'number' && typeof prev[k] === 'number' && prev[k] !== 0) {\n    drift[k] = Math.round(((current[k] - prev[k]) / prev[k]) * 1000) / 10;\n  }\n}\nreturn [{ json: { ...current, driftPct: drift, hasDrift: Object.values(drift).some(v => Math.abs(v) > 10) } }];"},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.code","typeVersion":2,"position":[3969,400],"id":"ff25d1a0-bddb-4f2c-bbda-ba4fc50a583f","name":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"operation":"csv","options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.convertToFile","typeVersion":1.1,"position":[4293,400],"id":"9af79fec-ee5b-4bd9-880c-e0ed0b48b085","name":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Request Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[4617,400],"id":"f7c15980-66b7-4c07-a1fa-37c1764b7e41","name":"Archive Row Snapshot","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"679af43d-8841-4d2f-966c-b8749a3dde15","name":"runAt","value":"={{ $now.toISO() }}","type":"string"},{"id":"e0290e5d-d5c6-44d8-86e7-428b365d18e8","name":"itemCount","value":"={{ $input.all().length }}","type":"number"},{"id":"aa598545-999c-49bb-ab60-f40390280b71","name":"status","value":"completed","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[4941,400],"id":"5fd8534a-939a-48f6-9f9c-c441fe9e2f9d","name":"Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Request Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[5265,400],"id":"62cc604c-d808-4b72-9786-15f0f7ecc63a","name":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#ai-ops","cachedResultName":"#ai-ops"},"text":"=✅ Answer user questions for Task Automation (01659) — run completed at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[5589,400],"id":"7ec04824-b43d-4447-a0f4-74aa68eec00e","name":"Send Summary to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"22ef89d9-51a4-41c0-a829-494e30502203","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"72df090b-9405-4b67-bd3c-a4865b415fe9","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"9a22cd24-e4e3-4ecb-a7ed-5fcd23559277","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[4941,1420],"id":"f7d52536-bd59-4d5e-8153-6f7853800e85","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#ai-ops","cachedResultName":"#ai-ops"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[5265,1420],"id":"93695baa-60ff-49a8-bea2-9233059b4d6f","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Request Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[5589,1420],"id":"e8199fe8-e2b6-4892-ad26-9a4757d999c6","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### When Chat Message Received\n\nOpens a hosted chat session; every user message starts an execution with `chatInput` + `sessionId`.\n\nNext: Stamp & Shape Request","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"7036cf10-480a-d929-57f8-026bcca55915","name":"Note: When Chat Message Received"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp & Shape Request\n\nShapes the item: writes `requestId`, `receivedAt`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Payload Valid?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"a91c143a-944e-0061-7631-d70f3d52ce6a","name":"Note: Stamp & Shape Request"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Payload Valid?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.requestId }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Answer from Knowledge Base · ②→ Record Rejected Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"c7b2b7c6-a408-a40e-6b9b-7920b85899f9","name":"Note: Payload Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Rejected Input\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,1030],"id":"ce41331c-72cd-49f2-7f72-8b9235d5be82","name":"Note: Record Rejected Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Answer from Knowledge Base\n\nThe AI brain: reads the input, decides which attached tools to call (and in what order), then composes the answer.\n\nPorts: ①→ Grounded Answer Found? · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,520],"id":"ffaa033f-6aa6-cb8e-cb9a-dff945e03df5","name":"Note: Answer from Knowledge Base"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenAI Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `gpt-4o-mini`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Answer from Knowledge Base** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenAI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,1090],"id":"0d69ced3-59b9-64b2-ba7f-1851967fbe88","name":"Note: OpenAI Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Knowledge Base Retriever\n\nExposes the vector index to the agent as a semantic-search tool.\n\nFeeds **Answer from Knowledge Base** as `tool`","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[939,1510],"id":"4440e6bd-e558-4475-1417-310eaf8d1864","name":"Note: Knowledge Base Retriever"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Query Embeddings\n\nEmbedding model — MUST be the same model for indexing and querying, or retrieval quality collapses.\n\nFeeds **Knowledge Base Retriever** as `embedding`\n\n🔑 OpenAI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[993,2020],"id":"b4c1b2d7-d03b-79fe-25bd-1e534f13e7dd","name":"Note: Query Embeddings"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Grounded Answer Found?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ !($json.output || '').includes('needsHuman') }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Deliver Answer via Slack · ②→ Log Knowledge Gap","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1317,520],"id":"8f017788-9cf0-4d29-ee7c-83686a3c15fb","name":"Note: Grounded Answer Found?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Deliver Answer via Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Load Previous Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1641,280],"id":"bccf7bb8-f222-da5f-cf25-e93f86b46221","name":"Note: Deliver Answer via Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Log Knowledge Gap\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Flag Gap to KB Owners · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1965,880],"id":"43e1b09a-c8cb-6258-1102-a49ea736da42","name":"Note: Log Knowledge Gap"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Flag Gap to KB Owners\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2613,880],"id":"0dc6ec2a-2f16-a3f0-b933-9f8986fc48aa","name":"Note: Flag Gap to KB Owners"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3585,520],"id":"4065e78d-7e44-f487-bdb3-97e0f85c8987","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3909,520],"id":"2c5ec055-9cc0-34bf-95c5-19a0d9859ba6","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4233,520],"id":"e11da80a-6f5f-e5bb-a321-a7bf2f9c50a6","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Summarize Run Stats · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4557,520],"id":"c33258ab-f567-156f-0696-fab912458070","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4881,520],"id":"3fa9605a-2f89-24c8-ad7d-4e3448440860","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5205,520],"id":"073e145d-adeb-ac1f-4719-e9770a34c301","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5529,520],"id":"fed91860-1ba3-7921-da4e-ef48bdba1674","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4881,1540],"id":"dcd6cda6-b27a-9b5f-d5e5-c13e2bbdd7c7","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5205,1540],"id":"834d716f-0bd4-2ae7-8b79-4b3a04bcb5de","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5529,1540],"id":"0df663cb-f7e1-e570-23da-d464a19ddf66","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Answer user questions for Task Automation (01659)\n\n**Pattern:** Chatbot Responder · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Chat\n\n## What it does\nAnswer user questions for Task Automation (01659). It responds live to chat messages.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual task automation is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWhen Chat Message Received → Stamp & Shape Request → Payload Valid? → Answer from Knowledge Base → Grounded Answer Found? → Deliver Answer via Slack → Load Previous Snapshot → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to chatbot responder without manual effort\n- Anyone automating task automation in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Improves response time\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; OpenAI API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"75d83e18-612d-2fee-1efa-5c6b175f904a","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-260],"id":"1e4defca-39f3-1b71-b532-904443befcc3","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-260],"id":"0e591580-0352-3b7e-e91e-d331dc2dbf14","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your task automation process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-260],"id":"b4558830-afcc-df1b-694c-9db95ff00ba9","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"When Chat Message Received":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Request","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Request":{"main":[[{"node":